Cloud computing: delivers computing services over the internet -> including common IT infrastructure such 
1. VM's 
2. Storage
3. Database
4. networking 

also expand the traditional IT offerings to include things like IoT, ML and AI. 

One main purpose of cloud computing is that you can scale up or down on IT infrastructure the same way that a traditional datacenter does. without the need of additional physical hardware. 

Compute power is how much processing your computer can do. 

Storage is the volume od data you can store on your computer. with cloud you can manage storage. 

